Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.For the rhubarb fool, whip the double cream in a bowl until soft peaks form when the whisk is removed. Whisk in the icing sugar, yoghurt, strawberry liqueur and vanilla seeds until well combined.Place the rhubarb onto a baking tray. Sprinkle with sugar and add the star anise and cinnamon stick. Bake in the oven for 5 minutes, or until the rhubarb is tender.Allow the rhubarb to cool slightly, and then fold into the fool mixture until well combined.For the biscuits, cream the butter and sugar in a bowl until light and fluffy.Stir in the egg and golden syrup. Add the flour, baking powder, ground ginger and stem ginger and mix until well combined.Roll the mixture into golfball-sized shapes and bake in the oven for 8-10 minutes, or until golden-brown.Spoon the fool mixture into pretty glasses and serve the biscuits alongside.